# v11-0-0-DUO: Google Drive OTA Update System

Replace the git-pull-based OTA pipeline with a Google Drive staging system. Updates are stored in versioned folders within the shared `staged_updates` directory. ODS operators assign target versions to devices via the dashboard, and devices download update files directly through the Archaeopteryx API (which proxies from Google Drive). No SSH keys, no git credentials, no repo clones on devices.

## Current Architecture (Being Replaced)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant D as Dashboard
    participant S as Server (Archaeopteryx)
    participant P as Player (Atlas)
    participant G as GitHub

    D->>S: POST /api/fleet-updates/push-all
    S->>P: Socket.IO: deploy_system_update
    P->>G: git pull origin main
    P->>P: cp scripts → /usr/local/bin/
    P->>P: systemctl restart
    P->>S: Socket.IO: update_status (complete)
```

## Proposed Architecture (v11-0-0-DUO)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant D as Dashboard
    participant S as Server (Archaeopteryx)
    participant P as Player (Atlas)
    participant GD as Google Drive

    D->>S: GET /api/staged-updates/versions
    S->>GD: List folders in staged_updates/
    GD-->>S: [v11-0-0-DUO, v10-5-1-PATCH, ...]
    S-->>D: Available versions

    D->>S: POST /api/staged-updates/assign
    Note over S: Sets target_version on player(s)

    D->>S: POST /api/fleet-updates/push-all
    S->>P: Socket.IO: deploy_system_update {target_version}

    P->>S: GET /api/staged-updates/manifest/{version}
    S->>GD: List files in staged_updates/{version}/
    GD-->>S: [manifest.json, scripts/..., config/...]
    S-->>P: File list + checksums

    P->>S: GET /api/staged-updates/download/{version}/{filename}
    S->>GD: Download file stream
    GD-->>S: File bytes
    S-->>P: File bytes

    P->>P: Verify checksums → apply → restart
    P->>S: Socket.IO: update_status {complete, new_version}
```

### Google Drive Folder Structure

```
ODS_Content_Storage/                    (ROOT_FOLDER_ID: existing)
  staged_updates/                       (STAGED_UPDATES_FOLDER_ID: 1RJDnpMnoUNCHP0H8Sw6B2g1hprmGGC2g)
    v11-0-0-DUO/
      manifest.json                     ← file list + sha256 checksums
      scripts/
        ods-system-update.sh
        ods-display-config.sh
        ...
      config/
        chromium-policy.json
        ...
      services/
        ods-player-ATLAS.service
        ...
    v10-5-1-PATCH/
      manifest.json
      scripts/
        ...
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### `manifest.json` Format (Per Version Folder)
> Each version folder **must** include a `manifest.json` at the root. This file is created manually when staging an update and lists every file in the version with its relative path and SHA-256 checksum. The server serves this to devices so they can verify downloads.
>
> ```json
> {
>   "version": "v11-0-0-DUO",
>   "created": "2026-03-06T08:00:00Z",
>   "files": [
>     { "path": "scripts/ods-system-update.sh", "sha256": "abc123..." },
>     { "path": "config/chromium-policy.json", "sha256": "def456..." }
>   ]
> }
> ```

